  "text": "For example, in one randomised trial [CITATION_1] three interventions -cognitive therapy, interpersonal therapy and pharmacotherapy -along with placebo control were studied in the treatment of adult depression. Therapeutic alliance was measured through structured observations at three time points during the treatment. Results showed that the quality of patient alliance was similar across all arms of the trial and independent of baseline symptoms. Alliance showed a strong independent effect on outcome in all arms (r = 0.46), explaining 19% of the outcome variance. Controlling for pre-treatment",
